<TITLE> JS watchdog finds Sadharan Bima Corporation 'off' by Tk 277 cr </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 8 (bdnews24.com)A parliamentary watchdog on Wednesday revealed financial irregularities totalling Tk 227 crore in state-run insurer Sadharan Bima Corporation. "The corporation has not initiated any move to realise the crores of taka in unpaid premiums," said MK Alamgir, chairman of the parliamentary standing committee on public undertaking. Alamgir told reporters, after a committee meeting, that innumerable audit objections had also been pending unresolved for years. "The situation is such that there is no one to look after these matters." "The committee has condemned the mismanagement and recommended disciplinary measures." Committee members TIM Fazle Rabbi Chowdhury, Khaledur Rahman Tito, Moinuddin Khan Badol, SK Abu Baker, Dhirendra Chandra Devnath, Fazlul Haq Harun and Zainul Abdin Farroque attended the meeting. Officials of finance ministry and the corporation were also present.
